<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-18T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-18T22:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.811/1041: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-19T11:00:00+08:00">November 19, 1938—11
                                    a.m.</date><lb/>[Received noon.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>72. Following letter dated November 18 has been received from Japanese
                            Consul General.</p>
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>“At the request of the Imperial Japanese military authorities, I have
                                the honor to inform you of the following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>‘Hereafter, navigation on the Han River is prohibited from
                                        necessity of military operations unless it is specially
                                        permitted by the military authorities.’</p>
                                </quote></p>
                            <pb facs="0209" n="205" xml:id="pg_205"/>
                            <p>It will be appreciated if you will be good enough to bring the above
                                regulation to the notice of your nationals concerned in the Wuhan
                                district at your earliest convenience.”</p>
                        </quote>
                        <p>Repeated to Chungking, Peiping.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>